I haven't been online in the last couple of months because I can't afford to get a new desktop computer. So I've kind of missed the huge growth the Arashi fandom has had in the last year. And with that, it has to be said:

HOTLINKING IS BAD. It is rude and makes my work meaningless.

What is hotlinking? It is directly copying and pasting the links to the files. You know, the actual hyperlink that directs you to the site where the file can be downloaded. I usually format these links as MU or MF. Copying and pasting those links are bad.

I would prefer that you link people to the ENTRIES, since most of my uploads are public. However if this continues, I would have to take action, as I have done in previous years.

If you re-upload, credit is a must. If you use elsewhere like in a fanvideo, for subbing purposes or for screencapping, a credit would be nice. Something like, "Thank you for the original video".

I'm currently working off my debts so I can afford to buy a new computer by the time I start university again. Until then, please behave nicely and I may actually want to come back instead of running away from the drama.

Thank you.

originally posted on vox.

anyone been getting this error?
Error running style: Died in S2::run_code running EntryPage::print(): Can't locate object method "new" via package "S2::Object" (perhaps you forgot to load "S2::Object"?) at (eval 1238)[/home/lj/src/s2/S2.pm:232] line 1827. 

if anyone is having trouble viewing other people's ljs or comms e.g. add ?style=mine to the end of the url to see it. like this: http://community.livejournal.com/a_ra_shi/?style=mine.

if there's already a ? mark in the url, add &style=mine to the end.

another useful modifier is ?format=light for journals with difficult to read layouts.

or you could just use your friends page.

if your own journal is borked, change the theme. only some themes are affected - i think the S2 ones? not sure of this.

edit: now fixed. this entry will stay up though, being full of useful tips and all.
